reviews.review_text: Me Likey I only saw 4 shows in 88 and all of which weren't off the charts and I considered 88 an off year but this one really shines with great=cohesive and inspired playing and a good clean recording. Would definitely add it to the collection.

Cool scene We had actual camp ground spaces up on the hill with bushes, parking, places to pitch tents and a fire pit.  No hassles, just a good ol time.  You could tell the band was having fun.  Sitting through David Lindley and Los Lobos plus the 2 dead sets made for a long day, so I skipped David on Sunday.  I was peaking during Wharf rat.
